               <head>Gulistan-i Rahmat, continuation</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Z̤amīmah-yi gulistān-i Raḥmat by Muḥammad Mustajāb Khān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n82236664 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064939" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4060-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656975.0x000001 viaf_286815242">Muḥammad Mustajāb Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656975.0x000001 viaf_286815242" type="supplied">محمّد مستجاب خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21974">Z̤amīmah-yi gulistān-i Raḥmat</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21974">ضميمهٴ گلستان رحمت</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Account of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7125" role="subject">Fayz̤ Allāh Khān</persName>, ruler of <name type="place">Rampur (Uttar Pradesh, India)</name> and his descendents, with special reference to the author's father, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_63646020" role="subject">Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Written in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1233</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1817-8</date>, at the suggestion of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f6688" role="pat">Charles Elliot</persName>, translator of the <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Gulistān-i Raḥmat</term>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                     <filiation>Copied from an original manuscript belonging to the library of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7730" role="oth">Qāz̤ī Tajammul Ḥusayn Khān</persName>, the <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">raʾīs</term> (gentleman or leader) of <name type="place">Moradabad (UP)</name>
                     </filiation>
